# c1
> openai.max
< cost <= $2.00
< latency <= 1m
@forward c2
@text <600

Propose one market-making experiment for Binance USDM.
Return:
pnl = <expected net ticks>
reason = <short explanation>
risk = <main failure mode>

# c2
> openrouter:openrouter/auto
@if pnl > 0 -> c3
@else -> c4

Evaluate %from c1.
Extract the expected net ticks into pnl and decide whether the idea deserves implementation.
Return exactly parseable lines:
pnl = <single numeric value>
reason = <short decision rationale>

# c3
> claude.code
@file -python strategy.py

Implement the accepted idea from %from c2 as pseudocode-level Python.
Include comments for data requirements, live safety limits, and stop conditions.
Return the requested file as an artifact section:
--- file: strategy.py ---

# c4
> claude.max
@file -markdown rejection_notes.md

Explain why the idea from %from c2 should be rejected or redesigned.
Suggest the next measurement before another implementation attempt.
